**Meta Platforms, Inc.: A Technology Giant Continues to Rise**

As ranked 30th in the Fortune 2024 list, Meta Platforms, Inc. has demonstrated remarkable resilience and adaptability in an ever-evolving technology landscape. The company, listed on the market under the ticker symbol META, has solidified its position within the Internet Services and Retailing industry, a sector that continues to shape the way people interact and conduct business.

Founded by Mark Zuckerberg, who also holds the title of CEO, Meta Platforms has maintained its profitable status, a testament to its ability to innovate and expand its offerings. Although the company has not experienced growth in jobs, its commitment to its employees is reflected in its substantial workforce of 67,317 individuals.

Meta Platforms has experienced a slight gain in rank, moving up one position from the previous year. This upward trend is indicative of the company's strategic approach to navigating the complexities of the technology sector. The company's market value, as of March 28, 2024, stood at $1.237 trillion, with a notable increase to $1.258 trillion as of July 15, 2024. This updated figure demonstrates the company's continued growth and attractiveness to investors.

In terms of financial performance, Meta Platforms reported revenues of $134.902 billion, representing a 15.7% increase from the previous year. This growth is complemented by a significant 68.5% increase in profits, which totaled $39.098 billion. The company's assets, valued at $229.623 billion, provide a solid foundation for its operations and future expansion.

As a globally recognized entity, Meta Platforms is featured in the Global 500 list, a distinction reserved for the world's most prominent companies. Additionally, the company has earned a spot on the World's Most Admired Companies list, a testament to its reputation and industry influence.

Headquartered in Menlo Park, California, Meta Platforms operates as a public company, with its investor relations and financial information available on its website, https://investor.fb.com. Under the leadership of Mark Zuckerberg, the company is poised to continue its upward trajectory, driven by innovation, strategic growth, and a commitment to its employees and stakeholders.